org.goobi.mq.processors

Class FinaliseStepProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.goobi.mq.ActiveMQProcessor
      • org.goobi.mq.processors.FinaliseStepProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javax.jms.MessageListener

    public class FinaliseStepProcessor
extends ActiveMQProcessor
    This is a web service interface to close steps. You have to provide the step id as “id”; you can add a field “message” which will be added to the wiki field.
    Author:
    Matthias Ronge <matthias.ronge@zeutschel.de>

    • Constructor Detail

      • FinaliseStepProcessor

        public FinaliseStepProcessor()
        The default constructor looks up the queue name to use in kitodo_config.properties. If that is not configured and “null” is passed to the super constructor, this will prevent ActiveMQDirector.registerListeners() from starting this service.

    • Method Detail

      • process

        protected void process(MapMessageObjectReader ticket)
                throws Exception
        This is the main routine processing incoming tickets. It gets an AktuelleSchritteForm object, sets it to the appropriate step which is retrieved from the database, appends the message − if any − to the wiki field, and executes the form’s the step close function.
        Specified by:
        process in class ActiveMQProcessor
        Parameters:
        ticket - the incoming message
        Throws:
        Exception
        See Also:
